This article is a transcript of a press briefing by Mike Froman, the Deputy National Security Advisor for International Economic Affairs, at the G-8 Summit in Italy. Froman discusses the topics that will be discussed at the summit, including the global economy, development issues, climate change, and geopolitical issues. He also mentions that declarations will be issued on the global economy, development in Africa, and climate change. Froman addresses questions about Iran, the lack of preparation by the Italian presidency, economic security and exit strategies, food security, and accountability. He also mentions that the bilat with President Hu of China may not happen.